# Rapolu-Renu-Akshaya-Xogene-React-Assessment

Create a new repository:
Go to GitHub account and create a new repository named "Rapolu-Renu-Akshaya-Xogene-React-Assessment" (or any name you prefer).

Clone the repository in VS Code:
Open VS Code.
Open the integrated terminal (Ctrl/Cmd + `).
Navigate to the directory where you want to clone the repository using the cd command.
Clone the repository using "git clone"

Create a new React application using Vite:
Once cloned, navigate into the project directory "cd Rapolu-Renu-Akshaya-Xogene-React-Assessment"
Use Vite to create a new React project "npm create vite@latest Xogene"
Follow the prompts to set up your Vite project. Choose react and javascript.

Install necessary dependencies:
Navigate into the newly created project directory "cd Xogene"
Install Axios "npm install axios"
Install React Router DOM (for client-side routing in React application) "npm install react-router-dom"

Now write the necessary code

Run the application locally:
Once you have written your code and installed dependencies, you can start the development server "npm run dev"
This command starts the Vite development server and typically opens the application in your default web browser at http://localhost:3000.
